Few hours to the end of the second lap of the Lockdown in Lagos, the Ogun States including the Federal Capital Territory, FCT Abuja, the Minister of Health, Prof Osagie Ehanire has said that the decision to extend COVID-19 lockdown was tailored according to the needs of every country. The Minister who spoke during a television programme also stated that the ministry has made recommendations to President Muhammed Buhari about the lockdown. He further noted that the President in his wisdom will decide if the lockdown will be lifted or not adding that “the modellings we have seen show that we have not gotten to the peak yet. We do think that the restriction of movement limits significantly the spread of the virus.” On the issue of testing, the minister said: “If your symptoms are not meeting the criteria, officials might turn you back. For the 40 health workers infected by COVID-19, he said: “Not all infected health workers got COVID-19 in the line of duty.” vanguard Dr Osagie Ehanire, the Minister of Health, on Sunday said President Mohammadu Buhari would determine when to lift the lockdown occasioned by th novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic in the country. April 27, 2020 In "News" Dr Osagie Ehanire, the Minister of Health, on Sunday said President Muhammadu Buhari would determine when to lift the lockdown occasioned by the novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic in the country. Ehanire said this on SundayPolitical on Channels Television in Abuja. The News Agency of Nigeria(NAN) reports that on April 13,… April 27, 2020 In "News" ---President to address nation again as extended lockdown expires By Johnbosco Agbakwuru ABUJA --- AS the second phase of the lockdown in Lagos, Ogun and the Federal Capital Territory, FCT, Abuja for 14 days expires Monday, President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday met with the Minister of Health, Dr Osagie Ehanire… April 26, 2020 In "News"